      "title": "East Germany (1979–1983)",
      "depth": 0,
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "After five years in La Habana, in 1979 he returned to East Germany."
            },
            {
              "text": "There he attended the “Escuela Juvenil Superior Wilhelm Pieck” (JHSWP), nicknamed the “Red Monastery,” next to Berlin and the Bogensee lake."
            },
            {
              "text": "There with other Chileans, he got a Marxist education for a year, studying Marxist and Leninist doctrine."
            },
            {
              "text": "He was a member of the “Unión de Jóvenes Demócratas”(UJD), of liberal inspiration."
            },
            {
              "text": "Ampuero remembered that “the JHSWP wasn’t a Punto Cero of military training like the ones that are in Cuba, Bulgaria, Libya, but a school of ideological thinking, but many others started believing in the idea that the only way was to resort to arms."
